# Autonomous Course Builder

A comprehensive, pedagogically-focused course creation platform that uses AI to generate syllabi, lecture notes, assignments, and grading rubrics with current industry references and quality assurance.

##  Project Overview

The AI Course Builder helps professors create complete, high-quality course packages by:
- **Generating pedagogically-sound syllabi** with current references and mandatory institutional appendices
- **Creating detailed 75-90 minute lecture content** with industry examples and interactive elements
- **Developing relevant assignments** with real-world applications and current case studies
- **Building comprehensive grading rubrics** for fair assessment and student growth

##  Architecture

### Technical Stack
- **Language Model**: OpenAI GPT-4o-mini (default), GPT-4o, GPT-4-turbo
- **Framework**: Streamlit + LangChain Integration
- **Search API**: Serper API for current references
- **Export**: ReportLab (PDF), python-docx (Word) with text fallbacks
- **Language**: Python 3.11+

### Modular Structure
```
📁 ai-course-builder/
├── 📄 app.py                 # Main Streamlit application with tab workflow
├── 📄 config.py              # Data models, SLOs, program-specific configurations
├── 📄 utils.py               # File processing, topic extraction, validation
├── 📄 serper_service.py      # Current references API integration
├── 📄 qa_agent.py            # 4-criteria quality assurance system
├── 📄 generators.py          # AI content generation classes
├── 📄 export_manager.py      # PDF/Word export with fallbacks
├── 📄 content_manager.py     # Version control and approval workflow
├── 📄 ui_components.py       # Reusable Streamlit components
├── 📄 requirements.txt       # Dependencies
└── 📄 README.md              # Documentation
```

### Key Features
- **Program-Specific Intelligence**: Separate SLOs and formatting for Undergraduate, Residential MBA, Kelley Direct
- **Mandatory Institutional Appendices**: Auto-appends required university policy language
- **Real-Time Quality Assurance**: 4-criteria evaluation with 80%+ pass threshold
- **Current References Integration**: Live Serper API for 2024-2025 content
- **Advanced System Prompt Control**: Professors can view/edit AI generation instructions
- **Interactive Lecture Design**: 75-90 minute sessions with engagement elements every 20 minutes
- **Syllabus-Lecture Topic Synchronization**: Automatic extraction and matching
- **Version Control**: Content approval workflow with edit tracking

##  Quick Start

### 1. Installation
```bash
git clone <repository-url>
cd ai-course-builder
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate  # Windows: .venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 2. API Keys Setup
**Required:**
- **OpenAI API Key** - [OpenAI Platform](https://platform.openai.com/)
- **Serper API Key** - [Serper.dev](https://serper.dev) (mandatory for current references)

### 3. Run Application
```bash
streamlit run app.py
```
Navigate to `http://localhost:8501`

